Information

Further Personal Information

Residence Frascati, ITA
Occupation Athlete
Languages Italian
Family Partner Luca Simoncelli

Sport Specific Information

When and where did you begin this sport? She began fencing at age six at a club in Monza, Italy.
Why this sport? Her mother took her to a fencing club and she fell in love with the sport.
Club / Team Frascati Scherma [ITA] / CS Carabinieri [ITA]:
Name of coach Luca Simoncelli [partner], ITA, from 2016; Andrea Cipressa [national]
Handedness Left

General Interest

Nicknames TsunAri [a play on the word 'tsunami']. (ariannaerrigo.it, 19 Jun 2017)
Hobbies Reading, dancing, surfing, travelling, drawing. (ariannaerrigo.it, 19 Jun 2017; avvenire.it, 19 Jul 2017)
Ambitions To win gold at the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo. (corriere.it, 04 Nov 2017)
Other information PAPAL VISIT
In 2014 she met Pope Francis at a ceremony in Rome, Italy, during the Christmas period. (corrieredicomo.it, 26 Dec 2014)
Awards and honours She received the Golden Necklace of Sports Merit in 2012 in Italy. (newsmondo.it, 06 Jun 2018)
